<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1762,2002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="77">
The general appearance of 
<taxonomicName box="[473,631,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eclipta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="faurei">
<emphasis box="[473,631,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="77">Eclipta faurei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very different from that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1873" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1873" box="[996,1366,1762,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eclipta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis box="[996,1200,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="77">Eclipta flavicollis</emphasis>
(Bates, 
<number box="[1301,1358,1762,1786]" pageId="11" pageNumber="77" value="1873.0">1873</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1386,1436,1762,1786]" pageId="11" pageNumber="77">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus): body shape; pronotal shape; elytral shape; legs (mainly hind ones). Those differences suggest that the species belong to a different and new genus. However, we examined a single female (without part of abdomen). Thus, the species is provisionally maintained in 
<taxonomicName box="[841,922,1870,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eclipta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[841,922,1870,1894]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="77">Eclipta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until it is possible to study more specimens (mainly males).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1762,2002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicName box="[199,358,1942,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eclipta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="faurei">
<emphasis box="[199,358,1942,1966]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="77">Eclipta faurei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described and it is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[877,1053,1942,1966]" name="French Guiana" pageId="11" pageNumber="77">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
. It is now recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1368,1436,1942,1966]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="77">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Rondônia) for the first time.
</paragraph>
